cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a meta-learning method for sample reweighting to address the issue of overfitting to biased training data with corrupted labels. The paper focuses on deep networks and their fitting capability to complex input patterns, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is evaluated on image classification tasks, indicating a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a meta-learner and the focus on learning bias correction suggest a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
